ROME Cristiano Ronaldo scored but wasteful Juventus had to settle for a 1-1 stalemate at home to Genoa to bring to an end the Italian champions' perfect start to the season on Saturday. With eight Serie A wins and two in the Champions League, Juve were all set to extend that fine run when Ronaldo put Massimiliano Allegri's men into a first half lead. But Juve were made to pay for failing to convert a hatful of chances when Daniel Bessa headed in a second half equaliser.  